`vim` is a much more sophisticated editor that should be distributed with most
Linux systems.

It is compatible with an older editor called `vi` that may be available on
older (10 years<) systems.

To write this file to disk, type colon, then w
:w

To exit, type colon, then q
:q

For more help, type colon, then help vimtutor
:help vimtutor
